    "description": "If you're a passionate Financial Analyst with drive and ambition, Grant Thornton India South Asia Partners in Gwalior is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Grant Thornton India South Asia Partners:\nGrant Thornton India South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in Credit Analysis\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Referral bonus program\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Grant Thornton India South Asia Partners!",
